## Controlled CPD theme taxonomy (11 categories)

Every extracted theme MUST map exactly to one of these. If a theme
cannot be mapped confidently, the file is FAILED ŌĆö never guess.

1. Governance & Trusteeship
2. Investments & ESG
3. DC Pensions & Master Trusts
4. Administration & Technology
5. Legal & Regulatory
6. Member Communications
7. Cyber Security & Data
8. Financial Management
9. Equality, Diversity & Inclusion
10. Industry Events & Networking
11. Other

"Other" is a valid mapping for a genuine CPD theme that fits no
specific category ŌĆö it is NOT a dumping ground for themes you are
unsure about. An unmappable or ambiguous theme means FAIL the file.

---

## What to extract from each agenda

| Field | Notes |
|-------|-------|
| `event_date` | The date the CPD activity takes place. ISO `yyyy-mm-dd`. |
| `duration_minutes` | Total scheduled duration, in minutes (integer). |
| `title` | The event / activity name. |
| `organiser` | The body running it (e.g. PMI, Aon, PASA, Professional Pensions). |
| `themes` | 1+ categories from the taxonomy above. First = primary. |
| `summary` | 1ŌĆō2 sentence plain-English summary of the agenda. |

Type and Role are intentionally left blank ŌĆö Jon sets those by hand
in the CPDTracker app.

If `event_date`, `duration_minutes`, `title` or `organiser` cannot be
determined with confidence, FAIL the file (`reason: ambiguous_data` or
the specific missing field). Do not guess.

