## Endpoint contract

POST JSON to `WEB_APP_URL`. Every request carries `token` =
`SHARED_SECRET` in the body (Apps Script cannot read HTTP headers).
All responses are HTTP 200; the real outcome is the `status` field.

### action: `ingest` ŌĆö a successfully extracted file

```json
{
  "token": "<SHARED_SECRET>",
  "action": "ingest",
  "record": {
    "event_date": "2026-05-19",
    "duration_minutes": 360,
    "title": "Professional Pensions Live 2026",
    "organiser": "Professional Pensions",
    "themes": ["DC Pensions & Master Trusts", "Investments & ESG"],
    "summary": "One-day conference on DC governance, investment and net zero.",
    "source_url": "https://example.com/agenda",
    "source_file_id": "<Drive file ID of the inbox file>",
    "source_filename": "ppl2026.pdf",
    "source_hash": "<SHA-256 hex of the file's bytes>"
  }
}
```

`source_url` only for `.txt`-URL files; otherwise omit or leave empty.

Response `status`: `created` | `merged` | `skipped_identical`
(file moved to `/processed/`), or `error` (file moved to `/failed/`).

### action: `fail` ŌĆö extraction failed before a record could be built

```json
{
  "token": "<SHARED_SECRET>",
  "action": "fail",
  "source_file_id": "<Drive file ID>",
  "source_filename": "broken.pdf",
  "source_hash": "<SHA-256 hex, or empty if unreadable>",
  "reason": "web_fetch_failed | parse_error | taxonomy_unmappable | ambiguous_data | ..."
}
```

The web app moves the file to `/failed/` and writes a
`<filename>.error.json` sidecar.

### action: `report_failures` ŌĆö once, at end of run

```json
{
  "token": "<SHARED_SECRET>",
  "action": "report_failures",
  "run_id": "2026-05-25T19:00",
  "failures": [
    { "filename": "broken.pdf", "reason": "parse_error" }
  ]
}
```

Send this ONLY if there were failures. The web app sends one
consolidated email to `ALERT_EMAIL`. An empty list sends nothing.

---

## Dedup ŌĆö decided by the web app, not the runner

The runner extracts and POSTs; the web app decides. For context only:

- same `source_hash` already recorded ŌåÆ `skipped_identical`
- same `logical_key` (`event_date | organiser | title`, normalised),
  different hash ŌåÆ additive `merged` (fills blank fields only)
- otherwise ŌåÆ `created`

## Idempotency

Before processing a file, SHA-256 hash it and check
`logs/manifest.json`. If that hash already appears there, the file was
already handled ŌĆö skip it (and let the web app's move stand). This is
what lets an interrupted run resume cleanly.
